spec: abc_extra73
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(abc)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html — Python abc module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/abc.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_abc.c"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends abc_extra72.zspec.zsdl."
    - "This spec covers: wave 244 theme — abc ABCMeta.__instancecheck__/__subclasscheck__/__new__ code attributes. NEW in extra73: ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_name=='__instancecheck__'; ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_argcount==2 (cls + instance); ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_name=='__subclasscheck__'; ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_argcount==2 (cls + subclass); ABCMeta.__new__.__code__.co_name=='__new__'; ABCMeta.__new__.__code__.co_argcount==4 (mcls + name + bases + namespace); ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_varnames.__class__.__name__=='tuple'; ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_varnames.__class__.__name__=='tuple'; ABCMeta.__new__.__code__.co_varnames.__class__.__name__=='tuple'. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_name == '__instancecheck__'. ABCMeta.__instancecheck__ is a Python method defined in abc.py; its code object co_name is '__instancecheck__'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_argcount == 2. __instancecheck__ takes cls and instance as positional parameters. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_name == '__subclasscheck__'. ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__ is a Python method defined in abc.py; its code object co_name is '__subclasscheck__'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_argcount == 2. __subclasscheck__ takes cls and subclass as positional parameters. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__new__.__code__.co_name == '__new__'. ABCMeta.__new__ is a Python method defined in abc.py; its code object co_name is '__new__'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__new__.__code__.co_argcount == 4. __new__ takes mcls, name, bases, and namespace as positional parameters (plus **kwargs). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_varnames.__class__.__name__ == 'tuple'. co_varnames is always a tuple in CPython code objects. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_varnames.__class__.__name__ == 'tuple'. co_varnames is always a tuple in CPython code objects. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__new__.__code__.co_varnames.__class__.__name__ == 'tuple'. co_varnames is always a tuple in CPython code objects. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

